      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-cou1-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.5 mm, medium 1.25 mm, fine 0.625 mm global element size) performed on the non-cannulated screw geometry. Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid convergence index (GCI) for the medium mesh: stiffness GCI = 0.8%, yield force GCI = 1.1%. Both well below the 5% threshold. Medium mesh selected for production runs.",
