      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled FEA software with documented QA procedures; regression test suite executed prior to production runs.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 used under a validated installation qualification (IQ/OQ) protocol. Version control via Git; regression suite of 47 benchmark cases executed with zero failures. SQA documentation archived in DePuy Synthes PLM system. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical or reference solutions used to verify solver implementation for contact mechanics and large-deformation elastoplasticity.",
      "rationale": "Three NAFEMS benchmark problems (LE1, NL1, contact patch test) verified against reference solutions to within 0.5%. Hertz contact problem reproduced to within 1.2%. All benchmarks documented in verification report VER-2023-047. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI < 5% for all primary QoIs on the production mesh.",
