  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this gap is accepted given the COU is explicitly scoped to ASTM F1717 compression-bending only and the regulatory submission does not claim coverage of torsional or lateral bending loading modes. All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance bounds (MAPE < 10%, E/uval < 1.96). Model risk level 3 with Medium assurance level is consistent with Class II device decision consequence. Package accepted for regulatory submission support.",
